{"$schema":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/master/Schemata/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json","version":"2.1.0","runs":[{"tool":{"driver":{"name":"Checkmarx One","version":"1.0","informationUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","rules":[{"id":"SQL Injection - 14517067005933136034 (sast)","name":"SQL Injection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s createLessonsForUser method executes an SQL query with execute, at line 52 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/UserService.java. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getName; this input is then read by the registrationOAUTH method at line 54 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/RegistrationController.java. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s createLessonsForUser method executes an SQL query with execute, at line 52 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/UserService.java. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getName; this input is then read by the registrationOAUTH method at line 54 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/RegistrationController.java. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s createLessonsForUser method executes an SQL query with execute, at line 52 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/UserService.java. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getName; this input is then read by the registrationOAUTH method at line 54 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/RegistrationController.java. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"SQL Injection","id":"SQL Injection - 14517067005933136034 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s createLessonsForUser method executes an SQL query with execute, at line 52 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/UserService.java. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getName; this input is then read by the registrationOAUTH method at line 54 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/users/RegistrationController.java. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Spring View SPEL Injection - 7925337960485979987 (sast)","name":"Spring View SPEL Injection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The user input provided in user at line 58 is inserted into a string, which is evaluated as an expression language statement by user in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/service/RestartLessonService.java at line 69 without being sanitized, resulting in the execution of expression language code from a potentially untrusted source.\n\nIn Spring applications, this may result in execution of Spring Expression Language (SPEL) code.\n\n","markdown":"The user input provided in user at line 58 is inserted into a string, which is evaluated as an expression language statement by user in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/service/RestartLessonService.java at line 69 without being sanitized, resulting in the execution of expression language code from a potentially untrusted source.\n\nIn Spring applications, this may result in execution of Spring Expression Language (SPEL) code.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The user input provided in user at line 58 is inserted into a string, which is evaluated as an expression language statement by user in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/service/RestartLessonService.java at line 69 without being sanitized, resulting in the execution of expression language code from a potentially untrusted source.\n\nIn Spring applications, this may result in execution of Spring Expression Language (SPEL) code.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"Spring View SPEL Injection","id":"Spring View SPEL Injection - 7925337960485979987 (sast)","description":"The user input provided in user at line 58 is inserted into a string, which is evaluated as an expression language statement by user in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/service/RestartLessonService.java at line 69 without being sanitized, resulting in the execution of expression language code from a potentially untrusted source.\n\nIn Spring applications, this may result in execution of Spring Expression Language (SPEL) code.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Client DOM XSS from AJAX - 5918789269251010216 (sast)","name":"Client DOM XSS from AJAX","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with append, at line 40 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe data is retrieved via an AJAX request by result in /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js at line 35.\n\n","markdown":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with append, at line 40 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe data is retrieved via an AJAX request by result in /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js at line 35.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with append, at line 40 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe data is retrieved via an AJAX request by result in /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js at line 35.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Client DOM XSS from AJAX","id":"Client DOM XSS from AJAX - 5918789269251010216 (sast)","description":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with append, at line 40 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe data is retrieved via an AJAX request by result in /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/lessons/xss/js/stored-xss.js at line 35.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39139 (sca)","name":"Cve202139139","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. A user is only affected if using the version out of the box with JDK 1.7u21 or below. However, this scenario can be adjusted easily to an external Xalan that works regardless of the version of the Java runtime. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. A user is only affected if using the version out of the box with JDK 1.7u21 or below. However, this scenario can be adjusted easily to an external Xalan that works regardless of the version of the Java runtime. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. A user is only affected if using the version out of the box with JDK 1.7u21 or below. However, this scenario can be adjusted easily to an external Xalan that works regardless of the version of the Java runtime. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139139","id":"CVE-2021-39139 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. A user is only affected if using the version out of the box with JDK 1.7u21 or below. However, this scenario can be adjusted easily to an external Xalan that works regardless of the version of the Java runtime. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21342 (sca)","name":"Cve202121342","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in a server-side forgery request. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in a server-side forgery request. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in a server-side forgery request. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121342","id":"CVE-2021-21342 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in a server-side forgery request. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"JWT No Signature Verification - 9038562562617823780 (sast)","name":"JWT No Signature Verification","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The JWT is not properly verified at the parse in 182 at the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTVotesEndpoint.java.\n\n","markdown":"The JWT is not properly verified at the parse in 182 at the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTVotesEndpoint.java.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The JWT is not properly verified at the parse in 182 at the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTVotesEndpoint.java.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"JWT No Signature Verification","id":"JWT No Signature Verification - 9038562562617823780 (sast)","description":"The JWT is not properly verified at the parse in 182 at the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTVotesEndpoint.java.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39154 (sca)","name":"Cve202139154","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139154","id":"CVE-2021-39154 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Jwt - jwt (sscs-secret-detection)","name":"Jwt","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Remove jwt eyJh*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault).","markdown":"Remove jwt eyJh*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Uncovered a JSON Web Token, which may lead to unauthorized access to web applications and sensitive user data."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Jwt","id":"Jwt - jwt (sscs-secret-detection)","description":"Uncovered a JSON Web Token, which may lead to unauthorized access to web applications and sensitive user data.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sscs-secret-detection"]}},{"id":"CVE-2017-7957 (sca)","name":"Cve20177957","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream through 1.4.9, when a certain denyTypes workaround is not used, mishandles attempts to create an instance of the primitive type \u0026#39;void\u0026#39; during unmarshalling, leading to a remote application crash, as demonstrated by an xstream.fromXML(\u0026#34;\u0026lt;void/\u0026gt;\u0026#34;) call.","markdown":"XStream through 1.4.9, when a certain denyTypes workaround is not used, mishandles attempts to create an instance of the primitive type \u0026#39;void\u0026#39; during unmarshalling, leading to a remote application crash, as demonstrated by an xstream.fromXML(\u0026#34;\u0026lt;void/\u0026gt;\u0026#34;) call."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream through 1.4.9, when a certain denyTypes workaround is not used, mishandles attempts to create an instance of the primitive type \u0026#39;void\u0026#39; during unmarshalling, leading to a remote application crash, as demonstrated by an xstream.fromXML(\u0026#34;\u0026lt;void/\u0026gt;\u0026#34;) call."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20177957","id":"CVE-2017-7957 (sca)","description":"XStream through 1.4.9, when a certain denyTypes workaround is not used, mishandles attempts to create an instance of the primitive type \u0026#39;void\u0026#39; during unmarshalling, leading to a remote application crash, as demonstrated by an xstream.fromXML(\u0026#34;\u0026lt;void/\u0026gt;\u0026#34;) call.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-29087 (containers)","name":"Cve202529087","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"In SQLite versions 3.44.0 through 3.44.3, 3.45.0 through 3.49.0, the \u0026#34;concat_ws()\u0026#34; SQL function can cause memory to be written beyond the end of a malloc-allocated buffer. If the separator argument is attacker-controlled and has a large string (e.g., 2MB or more), an Integer Overflow occurs in calculating the size of the result buffer, and thus malloc may not allocate enough memory. ","markdown":"In SQLite versions 3.44.0 through 3.44.3, 3.45.0 through 3.49.0, the \u0026#34;concat_ws()\u0026#34; SQL function can cause memory to be written beyond the end of a malloc-allocated buffer. If the separator argument is attacker-controlled and has a large string (e.g., 2MB or more), an Integer Overflow occurs in calculating the size of the result buffer, and thus malloc may not allocate enough memory. "},"fullDescription":{"text":"In SQLite versions 3.44.0 through 3.44.3, 3.45.0 through 3.49.0, the \u0026#34;concat_ws()\u0026#34; SQL function can cause memory to be written beyond the end of a malloc-allocated buffer. If the separator argument is attacker-controlled and has a large string (e.g., 2MB or more), an Integer Overflow occurs in calculating the size of the result buffer, and thus malloc may not allocate enough memory. "},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202529087","id":"CVE-2025-29087 (containers)","description":"In SQLite versions 3.44.0 through 3.44.3, 3.45.0 through 3.49.0, the \u0026#34;concat_ws()\u0026#34; SQL function can cause memory to be written beyond the end of a malloc-allocated buffer. If the separator argument is attacker-controlled and has a large string (e.g., 2MB or more), an Integer Overflow occurs in calculating the size of the result buffer, and thus malloc may not allocate enough memory. ","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2024-56406 (containers)","name":"Cve202456406","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A heap buffer overflow vulnerability was discovered in Perl. \n\nRelease branches 5.34, 5.36, 5.38 and 5.40 are affected, including development versions from 5.33.1 through 5.41.10.\n\nWhen there are non-ASCII bytes in the left-hand-side of the `tr` operator, `S_do_trans_invmap` can overflow the destination pointer `d`.\n\n   $ perl -e \u0026#39;$_ = \u0026#34;\\x{FF}\u0026#34; x 1000000; tr/\\xFF/\\x{100}/;\u0026#39; \n   Segmentation fault (core dumped)\n\nIt is believed that this vulnerability can enable Denial of Service and possibly Code Execution attacks on platforms that lack sufficient defenses.","markdown":"A heap buffer overflow vulnerability was discovered in Perl. \n\nRelease branches 5.34, 5.36, 5.38 and 5.40 are affected, including development versions from 5.33.1 through 5.41.10.\n\nWhen there are non-ASCII bytes in the left-hand-side of the `tr` operator, `S_do_trans_invmap` can overflow the destination pointer `d`.\n\n   $ perl -e \u0026#39;$_ = \u0026#34;\\x{FF}\u0026#34; x 1000000; tr/\\xFF/\\x{100}/;\u0026#39; \n   Segmentation fault (core dumped)\n\nIt is believed that this vulnerability can enable Denial of Service and possibly Code Execution attacks on platforms that lack sufficient defenses."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A heap buffer overflow vulnerability was discovered in Perl. \n\nRelease branches 5.34, 5.36, 5.38 and 5.40 are affected, including development versions from 5.33.1 through 5.41.10.\n\nWhen there are non-ASCII bytes in the left-hand-side of the `tr` operator, `S_do_trans_invmap` can overflow the destination pointer `d`.\n\n   $ perl -e \u0026#39;$_ = \u0026#34;\\x{FF}\u0026#34; x 1000000; tr/\\xFF/\\x{100}/;\u0026#39; \n   Segmentation fault (core dumped)\n\nIt is believed that this vulnerability can enable Denial of Service and possibly Code Execution attacks on platforms that lack sufficient defenses."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202456406","id":"CVE-2024-56406 (containers)","description":"A heap buffer overflow vulnerability was discovered in Perl. \n\nRelease branches 5.34, 5.36, 5.38 and 5.40 are affected, including development versions from 5.33.1 through 5.41.10.\n\nWhen there are non-ASCII bytes in the left-hand-side of the `tr` operator, `S_do_trans_invmap` can overflow the destination pointer `d`.\n\n   $ perl -e \u0026#39;$_ = \u0026#34;\\x{FF}\u0026#34; x 1000000; tr/\\xFF/\\x{100}/;\u0026#39; \n   Segmentation fault (core dumped)\n\nIt is believed that this vulnerability can enable Denial of Service and possibly Code Execution attacks on platforms that lack sufficient defenses.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-6020 (containers)","name":"Cve20256020","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A flaw was found in linux-pam. The module pam_namespace may use access user-controlled paths without proper protection, allowing local users to elevate their privileges to root via multiple symlink attacks and race conditions.","markdown":"A flaw was found in linux-pam. The module pam_namespace may use access user-controlled paths without proper protection, allowing local users to elevate their privileges to root via multiple symlink attacks and race conditions."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A flaw was found in linux-pam. The module pam_namespace may use access user-controlled paths without proper protection, allowing local users to elevate their privileges to root via multiple symlink attacks and race conditions."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20256020","id":"CVE-2025-6020 (containers)","description":"A flaw was found in linux-pam. The module pam_namespace may use access user-controlled paths without proper protection, allowing local users to elevate their privileges to root via multiple symlink attacks and race conditions.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-0395 (containers)","name":"Cve20250395","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"When the `assert()` function in the GNU C Library versions 2.14 through 2.40 fails, it does not allocate enough space for the assertion failure message string and size information, which may lead to a buffer overflow if the message string size aligns to page size.","markdown":"When the `assert()` function in the GNU C Library versions 2.14 through 2.40 fails, it does not allocate enough space for the assertion failure message string and size information, which may lead to a buffer overflow if the message string size aligns to page size."},"fullDescription":{"text":"When the `assert()` function in the GNU C Library versions 2.14 through 2.40 fails, it does not allocate enough space for the assertion failure message string and size information, which may lead to a buffer overflow if the message string size aligns to page size."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20250395","id":"CVE-2025-0395 (containers)","description":"When the `assert()` function in the GNU C Library versions 2.14 through 2.40 fails, it does not allocate enough space for the assertion failure message string and size information, which may lead to a buffer overflow if the message string size aligns to page size.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2024-8176 (containers)","name":"Cve20248176","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A stack overflow vulnerability exists in the libexpat library due to the way it handles recursive entity expansion in XML documents. When parsing an XML document with deeply nested entity references, libexpat can be forced to recurse indefinitely, exhausting the stack space and causing a crash. This issue could lead to Denial of Service (DoS) or, in some cases, exploitable memory corruption, depending on the environment and library usage. This issue affects libexpat versions prior to 2.7.0.","markdown":"A stack overflow vulnerability exists in the libexpat library due to the way it handles recursive entity expansion in XML documents. When parsing an XML document with deeply nested entity references, libexpat can be forced to recurse indefinitely, exhausting the stack space and causing a crash. This issue could lead to Denial of Service (DoS) or, in some cases, exploitable memory corruption, depending on the environment and library usage. This issue affects libexpat versions prior to 2.7.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A stack overflow vulnerability exists in the libexpat library due to the way it handles recursive entity expansion in XML documents. When parsing an XML document with deeply nested entity references, libexpat can be forced to recurse indefinitely, exhausting the stack space and causing a crash. This issue could lead to Denial of Service (DoS) or, in some cases, exploitable memory corruption, depending on the environment and library usage. This issue affects libexpat versions prior to 2.7.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20248176","id":"CVE-2024-8176 (containers)","description":"A stack overflow vulnerability exists in the libexpat library due to the way it handles recursive entity expansion in XML documents. When parsing an XML document with deeply nested entity references, libexpat can be forced to recurse indefinitely, exhausting the stack space and causing a crash. This issue could lead to Denial of Service (DoS) or, in some cases, exploitable memory corruption, depending on the environment and library usage. This issue affects libexpat versions prior to 2.7.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-31115 (containers)","name":"Cve202531115","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XZ Utils provides a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. In XZ Utils versions 5.3.3alpha through 5.8.0, the multithreaded \u0026#34;.xz\u0026#34; decoder in \u0026#34;liblzma\u0026#34; has a bug where invalid input can result in a crash. The effects include Heap Use After Free and writing to an address based on the null pointer plus an offset. Applications and libraries that use the \u0026#34;lzma_stream_decoder_mt\u0026#34; function are affected. The bug has been fixed in XZ Utils 5.8.1, and the fix has been committed to the v5.4, v5.6, v5.8, and master branches in the xz Git repository. No new release packages will be made from the old stable branches, but a standalone patch is available that applies to all affected releases.","markdown":"XZ Utils provides a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. In XZ Utils versions 5.3.3alpha through 5.8.0, the multithreaded \u0026#34;.xz\u0026#34; decoder in \u0026#34;liblzma\u0026#34; has a bug where invalid input can result in a crash. The effects include Heap Use After Free and writing to an address based on the null pointer plus an offset. Applications and libraries that use the \u0026#34;lzma_stream_decoder_mt\u0026#34; function are affected. The bug has been fixed in XZ Utils 5.8.1, and the fix has been committed to the v5.4, v5.6, v5.8, and master branches in the xz Git repository. No new release packages will be made from the old stable branches, but a standalone patch is available that applies to all affected releases."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XZ Utils provides a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. In XZ Utils versions 5.3.3alpha through 5.8.0, the multithreaded \u0026#34;.xz\u0026#34; decoder in \u0026#34;liblzma\u0026#34; has a bug where invalid input can result in a crash. The effects include Heap Use After Free and writing to an address based on the null pointer plus an offset. Applications and libraries that use the \u0026#34;lzma_stream_decoder_mt\u0026#34; function are affected. The bug has been fixed in XZ Utils 5.8.1, and the fix has been committed to the v5.4, v5.6, v5.8, and master branches in the xz Git repository. No new release packages will be made from the old stable branches, but a standalone patch is available that applies to all affected releases."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202531115","id":"CVE-2025-31115 (containers)","description":"XZ Utils provides a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. In XZ Utils versions 5.3.3alpha through 5.8.0, the multithreaded \u0026#34;.xz\u0026#34; decoder in \u0026#34;liblzma\u0026#34; has a bug where invalid input can result in a crash. The effects include Heap Use After Free and writing to an address based on the null pointer plus an offset. Applications and libraries that use the \u0026#34;lzma_stream_decoder_mt\u0026#34; function are affected. The bug has been fixed in XZ Utils 5.8.1, and the fix has been committed to the v5.4, v5.6, v5.8, and master branches in the xz Git repository. No new release packages will be made from the old stable branches, but a standalone patch is available that applies to all affected releases.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-6965 (containers)","name":"Cve20256965","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"There exists a vulnerability in SQLite versions through 3.44.4 and 3.45.x through 3.49.2, and 3.50.x through 3.50.1, where the number of aggregate terms could exceed the number of columns available. This could lead to a memory corruption issue. ","markdown":"There exists a vulnerability in SQLite versions through 3.44.4 and 3.45.x through 3.49.2, and 3.50.x through 3.50.1, where the number of aggregate terms could exceed the number of columns available. This could lead to a memory corruption issue. "},"fullDescription":{"text":"There exists a vulnerability in SQLite versions through 3.44.4 and 3.45.x through 3.49.2, and 3.50.x through 3.50.1, where the number of aggregate terms could exceed the number of columns available. This could lead to a memory corruption issue. "},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20256965","id":"CVE-2025-6965 (containers)","description":"There exists a vulnerability in SQLite versions through 3.44.4 and 3.45.x through 3.49.2, and 3.50.x through 3.50.1, where the number of aggregate terms could exceed the number of columns available. This could lead to a memory corruption issue. ","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"Private-Key - private-key (sscs-secret-detection)","name":"Private-Key","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Remove private-key \";\n *** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault).","markdown":"Remove private-key \";\n *** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Identified a Private Key, which may compromise cryptographic security and sensitive data encryption."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Private-Key","id":"Private-Key - private-key (sscs-secret-detection)","description":"Identified a Private Key, which may compromise cryptographic security and sensitive data encryption.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sscs-secret-detection"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39153 (sca)","name":"Cve202139153","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream, if using the version out of the box with Java runtime version 14 to 8 or with JavaFX installed. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream, if using the version out of the box with Java runtime version 14 to 8 or with JavaFX installed. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream, if using the version out of the box with Java runtime version 14 to 8 or with JavaFX installed. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139153","id":"CVE-2021-39153 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream, if using the version out of the box with Java runtime version 14 to 8 or with JavaFX installed. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref - 14846722546022341732 (sast)","name":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The parseXml loads and parses XML using createXMLStreamReader, at line 97 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/CommentsCache.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, commentStr, at line 69 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/SimpleXXE.java. Note that createXMLStreamReader is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n","markdown":"The parseXml loads and parses XML using createXMLStreamReader, at line 97 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/CommentsCache.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, commentStr, at line 69 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/SimpleXXE.java. Note that createXMLStreamReader is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The parseXml loads and parses XML using createXMLStreamReader, at line 97 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/CommentsCache.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, commentStr, at line 69 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/SimpleXXE.java. Note that createXMLStreamReader is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref","id":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref - 14846722546022341732 (sast)","description":"The parseXml loads and parses XML using createXMLStreamReader, at line 97 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/CommentsCache.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, commentStr, at line 69 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/xxe/SimpleXXE.java. Note that createXMLStreamReader is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Relative Path Traversal - 11267356716587554023 (sast)","name":"Relative Path Traversal","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method uploadFileHandler at line 38 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadFix.java gets dynamic data from the username element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in cleanupAndCreateDirectoryForUser at line 66 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadBase.java. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n","markdown":"Method uploadFileHandler at line 38 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadFix.java gets dynamic data from the username element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in cleanupAndCreateDirectoryForUser at line 66 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadBase.java. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method uploadFileHandler at line 38 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadFix.java gets dynamic data from the username element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in cleanupAndCreateDirectoryForUser at line 66 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadBase.java. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Relative Path Traversal","id":"Relative Path Traversal - 11267356716587554023 (sast)","description":"Method uploadFileHandler at line 38 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadFix.java gets dynamic data from the username element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in cleanupAndCreateDirectoryForUser at line 66 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/pathtraversal/ProfileUploadBase.java. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-40151 (sca)","name":"Cve202240151","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Those using Xstream to serialize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a Denial of Service attack and affects versions prior to 1.4.20.","markdown":"Those using Xstream to serialize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a Denial of Service attack and affects versions prior to 1.4.20."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Those using Xstream to serialize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a Denial of Service attack and affects versions prior to 1.4.20."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202240151","id":"CVE-2022-40151 (sca)","description":"Those using Xstream to serialize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a Denial of Service attack and affects versions prior to 1.4.20.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Deserialization of Untrusted Data - 9920599561530748290 (sast)","name":"Deserialization of Untrusted Data","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The serialized object payload processed in completed in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 43 is deserialized by fromXML in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 60.\n\n","markdown":"The serialized object payload processed in completed in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 43 is deserialized by fromXML in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 60.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The serialized object payload processed in completed in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 43 is deserialized by fromXML in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 60.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Deserialization of Untrusted Data","id":"Deserialization of Untrusted Data - 9920599561530748290 (sast)","description":"The serialized object payload processed in completed in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 43 is deserialized by fromXML in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/vulnerablecomponents/VulnerableComponentsLesson.java at line 60.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Reflected XSS - 16772998409937314312 (sast)","name":"Reflected XSS","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with appendChild, at line 104 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input get, which is read by the Lambda method at line 469 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","markdown":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with appendChild, at line 104 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input get, which is read by the Lambda method at line 469 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with appendChild, at line 104 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input get, which is read by the Lambda method at line 469 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Reflected XSS","id":"Reflected XSS - 16772998409937314312 (sast)","description":"The method Lambda embeds untrusted data in generated output with appendChild, at line 104 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input get, which is read by the Lambda method at line 469 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/require.min.js. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21341 (sca)","name":"Cve202121341","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121341","id":"CVE-2021-21341 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-46701 (sca)","name":"Cve202546701","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Improper Handling of Case Sensitivity vulnerability in Apache Tomcat\u0026#39;s GCI servlet allows security constraint bypass of security constraints that apply to the \u0026#34;pathInfo\u0026#34; component of a URI mapped to the CGI servlet.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.6, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.40, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.104.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.7, 10.1.41 or 9.0.105, which fixes the issue.","markdown":"Improper Handling of Case Sensitivity vulnerability in Apache Tomcat\u0026#39;s GCI servlet allows security constraint bypass of security constraints that apply to the \u0026#34;pathInfo\u0026#34; component of a URI mapped to the CGI servlet.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.6, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.40, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.104.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.7, 10.1.41 or 9.0.105, which fixes the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Improper Handling of Case Sensitivity vulnerability in Apache Tomcat\u0026#39;s GCI servlet allows security constraint bypass of security constraints that apply to the \u0026#34;pathInfo\u0026#34; component of a URI mapped to the CGI servlet.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.6, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.40, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.104.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.7, 10.1.41 or 9.0.105, which fixes the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202546701","id":"CVE-2025-46701 (sca)","description":"Improper Handling of Case Sensitivity vulnerability in Apache Tomcat\u0026#39;s GCI servlet allows security constraint bypass of security constraints that apply to the \u0026#34;pathInfo\u0026#34; component of a URI mapped to the CGI servlet.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.6, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.40, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.104.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.7, 10.1.41 or 9.0.105, which fixes the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Reflected XSS - 8481125285487743346 (sast)","name":"Reflected XSS","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The method resetPassword embeds untrusted data in generated output with modelAndView, at line 115 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input link, which is read by the resetPassword method at line 103 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","markdown":"The method resetPassword embeds untrusted data in generated output with modelAndView, at line 115 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input link, which is read by the resetPassword method at line 103 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The method resetPassword embeds untrusted data in generated output with modelAndView, at line 115 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input link, which is read by the resetPassword method at line 103 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Reflected XSS","id":"Reflected XSS - 8481125285487743346 (sast)","description":"The method resetPassword embeds untrusted data in generated output with modelAndView, at line 115 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input link, which is read by the resetPassword method at line 103 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/passwordreset/ResetLinkAssignment.java. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2013-7285 (sca)","name":"Cve20137285","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Xstream API versions up to 1.4.6, if the security framework has not been initialized, may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating the processed input stream when unmarshaling XML or any supported format. e.g. JSON.","markdown":"Xstream API versions up to 1.4.6, if the security framework has not been initialized, may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating the processed input stream when unmarshaling XML or any supported format. e.g. JSON."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Xstream API versions up to 1.4.6, if the security framework has not been initialized, may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating the processed input stream when unmarshaling XML or any supported format. e.g. JSON."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20137285","id":"CVE-2013-7285 (sca)","description":"Xstream API versions up to 1.4.6, if the security framework has not been initialized, may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating the processed input stream when unmarshaling XML or any supported format. e.g. JSON.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-26217 (sca)","name":"Cve202026217","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream before version 1.4.14 is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution.The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands only by manipulating the processed input stream. Only users who rely on blocklists are affected. Anyone using XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework allowlist is not affected. The linked advisory provides code workarounds for users who cannot upgrade. The issue is fixed in version 1.4.14, and patched in versions 1.4.14-jdk7 and 1.4.14-java7.","markdown":"XStream before version 1.4.14 is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution.The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands only by manipulating the processed input stream. Only users who rely on blocklists are affected. Anyone using XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework allowlist is not affected. The linked advisory provides code workarounds for users who cannot upgrade. The issue is fixed in version 1.4.14, and patched in versions 1.4.14-jdk7 and 1.4.14-java7."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream before version 1.4.14 is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution.The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands only by manipulating the processed input stream. Only users who rely on blocklists are affected. Anyone using XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework allowlist is not affected. The linked advisory provides code workarounds for users who cannot upgrade. The issue is fixed in version 1.4.14, and patched in versions 1.4.14-jdk7 and 1.4.14-java7."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202026217","id":"CVE-2020-26217 (sca)","description":"XStream before version 1.4.14 is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution.The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to run arbitrary shell commands only by manipulating the processed input stream. Only users who rely on blocklists are affected. Anyone using XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework allowlist is not affected. The linked advisory provides code workarounds for users who cannot upgrade. The issue is fixed in version 1.4.14, and patched in versions 1.4.14-jdk7 and 1.4.14-java7.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39146 (sca)","name":"Cve202139146","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139146","id":"CVE-2021-39146 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"JWT Use Of None Algorithm - 8599108152065152727 (sast)","name":"JWT Use Of None Algorithm","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The None algorithm is used during the JWT creation by compact at /WebGoat-main/src/test/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTSecretKeyEndpointTest.java in line 133. \n\n","markdown":"The None algorithm is used during the JWT creation by compact at /WebGoat-main/src/test/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTSecretKeyEndpointTest.java in line 133. \n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The None algorithm is used during the JWT creation by compact at /WebGoat-main/src/test/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTSecretKeyEndpointTest.java in line 133. \n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"JWT Use Of None Algorithm","id":"JWT Use Of None Algorithm - 8599108152065152727 (sast)","description":"The None algorithm is used during the JWT creation by compact at /WebGoat-main/src/test/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTSecretKeyEndpointTest.java in line 133. \n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-43859 (sca)","name":"Cve202143859","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is an open source java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.19 may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. XStream 1.4.19 monitors and accumulates the time it takes to add elements to collections and throws an exception if a set threshold is exceeded. Users are advised to upgrade as soon as possible. Users unable to upgrade may set the NO_REFERENCE mode to prevent recursion. See GHSA-rmr5-cpv2-vgjf for further details on a workaround if an upgrade is not possible.","markdown":"XStream is an open source java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.19 may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. XStream 1.4.19 monitors and accumulates the time it takes to add elements to collections and throws an exception if a set threshold is exceeded. Users are advised to upgrade as soon as possible. Users unable to upgrade may set the NO_REFERENCE mode to prevent recursion. See GHSA-rmr5-cpv2-vgjf for further details on a workaround if an upgrade is not possible."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is an open source java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.19 may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. XStream 1.4.19 monitors and accumulates the time it takes to add elements to collections and throws an exception if a set threshold is exceeded. Users are advised to upgrade as soon as possible. Users unable to upgrade may set the NO_REFERENCE mode to prevent recursion. See GHSA-rmr5-cpv2-vgjf for further details on a workaround if an upgrade is not possible."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202143859","id":"CVE-2021-43859 (sca)","description":"XStream is an open source java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.19 may allow a remote attacker to allocate 100% CPU time on the target system depending on CPU type or parallel execution of such a payload resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream. XStream 1.4.19 monitors and accumulates the time it takes to add elements to collections and throws an exception if a set threshold is exceeded. Users are advised to upgrade as soon as possible. Users unable to upgrade may set the NO_REFERENCE mode to prevent recursion. See GHSA-rmr5-cpv2-vgjf for further details on a workaround if an upgrade is not possible.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39152 (sca)","name":"Cve202139152","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream with a Java runtime version 14 to 8. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the [Security Framework](https://x-stream.github.io/security.html#framework), you will have to use at least version 1.4.18.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream with a Java runtime version 14 to 8. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the [Security Framework](https://x-stream.github.io/security.html#framework), you will have to use at least version 1.4.18."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream with a Java runtime version 14 to 8. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the [Security Framework](https://x-stream.github.io/security.html#framework), you will have to use at least version 1.4.18."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139152","id":"CVE-2021-39152 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream with a Java runtime version 14 to 8. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the [Security Framework](https://x-stream.github.io/security.html#framework), you will have to use at least version 1.4.18.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-22235 (sca)","name":"Cve202522235","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; creates a matcher for \u0026#34;null/**\u0026#34; if the actuator endpoint, for which the \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; has been created, is disabled or not exposed. Your application may be affected by this if all the following conditions are met: *You use Spring Security * \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; has been used in a Spring Security chain configuration * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; references is disabled or not exposed via web * Your application handles requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; and this path needs protection You are not affected if any of the following is true: * You don\u0026#39;t use Spring Security * You don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; refers to is enabled and is exposed * Your application does not handle requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; or this path does not need protection. The issue affects org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure versions through 2.7.24.2, 3.0.0 through 3.1.15.2, 3.2.0 through 3.2.13.2, 3.3.0 through 3.3.10, and 3.4.0 through 3.4.4.","markdown":"The \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; creates a matcher for \u0026#34;null/**\u0026#34; if the actuator endpoint, for which the \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; has been created, is disabled or not exposed. Your application may be affected by this if all the following conditions are met: *You use Spring Security * \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; has been used in a Spring Security chain configuration * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; references is disabled or not exposed via web * Your application handles requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; and this path needs protection You are not affected if any of the following is true: * You don\u0026#39;t use Spring Security * You don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; refers to is enabled and is exposed * Your application does not handle requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; or this path does not need protection. The issue affects org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure versions through 2.7.24.2, 3.0.0 through 3.1.15.2, 3.2.0 through 3.2.13.2, 3.3.0 through 3.3.10, and 3.4.0 through 3.4.4."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; creates a matcher for \u0026#34;null/**\u0026#34; if the actuator endpoint, for which the \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; has been created, is disabled or not exposed. Your application may be affected by this if all the following conditions are met: *You use Spring Security * \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; has been used in a Spring Security chain configuration * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; references is disabled or not exposed via web * Your application handles requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; and this path needs protection You are not affected if any of the following is true: * You don\u0026#39;t use Spring Security * You don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; refers to is enabled and is exposed * Your application does not handle requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; or this path does not need protection. The issue affects org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure versions through 2.7.24.2, 3.0.0 through 3.1.15.2, 3.2.0 through 3.2.13.2, 3.3.0 through 3.3.10, and 3.4.0 through 3.4.4."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202522235","id":"CVE-2025-22235 (sca)","description":"The \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; creates a matcher for \u0026#34;null/**\u0026#34; if the actuator endpoint, for which the \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; has been created, is disabled or not exposed. Your application may be affected by this if all the following conditions are met: *You use Spring Security * \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; has been used in a Spring Security chain configuration * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest\u0026#34; references is disabled or not exposed via web * Your application handles requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; and this path needs protection You are not affected if any of the following is true: * You don\u0026#39;t use Spring Security * You don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; * The endpoint which \u0026#34;EndpointRequest.to()\u0026#34; refers to is enabled and is exposed * Your application does not handle requests to \u0026#34;/null\u0026#34; or this path does not need protection. The issue affects org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure versions through 2.7.24.2, 3.0.0 through 3.1.15.2, 3.2.0 through 3.2.13.2, 3.3.0 through 3.3.10, and 3.4.0 through 3.4.4.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-31651 (sca)","name":"Cve202531651","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Improper Neutralization of Escape, Meta, or Control Sequences vulnerability was found within Apache Tomcat. For a subset of unlikely rewrite rule configurations, it was possible for a specially crafted request to bypass some rewrite rules. If those rewrite rules effectively enforced security constraints, those constraints could be bypassed.\n\nThis issue affects the Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.5, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.39 and from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.102.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to the following versions 9.0.104 or later, 10.1.40 or later and 11.0.6 or later, which fixes the issue.","markdown":"Improper Neutralization of Escape, Meta, or Control Sequences vulnerability was found within Apache Tomcat. For a subset of unlikely rewrite rule configurations, it was possible for a specially crafted request to bypass some rewrite rules. If those rewrite rules effectively enforced security constraints, those constraints could be bypassed.\n\nThis issue affects the Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.5, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.39 and from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.102.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to the following versions 9.0.104 or later, 10.1.40 or later and 11.0.6 or later, which fixes the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Improper Neutralization of Escape, Meta, or Control Sequences vulnerability was found within Apache Tomcat. For a subset of unlikely rewrite rule configurations, it was possible for a specially crafted request to bypass some rewrite rules. If those rewrite rules effectively enforced security constraints, those constraints could be bypassed.\n\nThis issue affects the Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.5, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.39 and from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.102.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to the following versions 9.0.104 or later, 10.1.40 or later and 11.0.6 or later, which fixes the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202531651","id":"CVE-2025-31651 (sca)","description":"Improper Neutralization of Escape, Meta, or Control Sequences vulnerability was found within Apache Tomcat. For a subset of unlikely rewrite rule configurations, it was possible for a specially crafted request to bypass some rewrite rules. If those rewrite rules effectively enforced security constraints, those constraints could be bypassed.\n\nThis issue affects the Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.5, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.39 and from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.102.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to the following versions 9.0.104 or later, 10.1.40 or later and 11.0.6 or later, which fixes the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-22228 (sca)","name":"Cve202522228","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The Spring Security \u0026#34;BCryptPasswordEncoder.matches(CharSequence, String)\u0026#34; method may incorrectly return true for passwords longer than 72 characters, even if only the first 72 characters match. This issue affects open-source versions through 6.3.7, 6.4.0-M1 through 6.4.3, and 6.5.0-M1 through 6.5.0-M2.","markdown":"The Spring Security \u0026#34;BCryptPasswordEncoder.matches(CharSequence, String)\u0026#34; method may incorrectly return true for passwords longer than 72 characters, even if only the first 72 characters match. This issue affects open-source versions through 6.3.7, 6.4.0-M1 through 6.4.3, and 6.5.0-M1 through 6.5.0-M2."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The Spring Security \u0026#34;BCryptPasswordEncoder.matches(CharSequence, String)\u0026#34; method may incorrectly return true for passwords longer than 72 characters, even if only the first 72 characters match. This issue affects open-source versions through 6.3.7, 6.4.0-M1 through 6.4.3, and 6.5.0-M1 through 6.5.0-M2."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202522228","id":"CVE-2025-22228 (sca)","description":"The Spring Security \u0026#34;BCryptPasswordEncoder.matches(CharSequence, String)\u0026#34; method may incorrectly return true for passwords longer than 72 characters, even if only the first 72 characters match. This issue affects open-source versions through 6.3.7, 6.4.0-M1 through 6.4.3, and 6.5.0-M1 through 6.5.0-M2.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2024-57699 (sca)","name":"Cve202457699","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A security issue was found in Netplex Json-smart. When loading a specially crafted JSON input, containing a large number of \u0026#34;{\u0026#34;, a stack exhaustion can be triggered, which could allow an attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS). This issue affects \u0026#34;net.minidev:json-smart\u0026#34; versions 2.5.0 through 2.5.1. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370.","markdown":"A security issue was found in Netplex Json-smart. When loading a specially crafted JSON input, containing a large number of \u0026#34;{\u0026#34;, a stack exhaustion can be triggered, which could allow an attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS). This issue affects \u0026#34;net.minidev:json-smart\u0026#34; versions 2.5.0 through 2.5.1. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A security issue was found in Netplex Json-smart. When loading a specially crafted JSON input, containing a large number of \u0026#34;{\u0026#34;, a stack exhaustion can be triggered, which could allow an attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS). This issue affects \u0026#34;net.minidev:json-smart\u0026#34; versions 2.5.0 through 2.5.1. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202457699","id":"CVE-2024-57699 (sca)","description":"A security issue was found in Netplex Json-smart. When loading a specially crafted JSON input, containing a large number of \u0026#34;{\u0026#34;, a stack exhaustion can be triggered, which could allow an attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS). This issue affects \u0026#34;net.minidev:json-smart\u0026#34; versions 2.5.0 through 2.5.1. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2024-47072 (sca)","name":"Cve202447072","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a Denial of Service(DoS) only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;. XStream has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. This issue affects com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream versions prior to 1.4.21. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the \u0026#34;StackOverflowError\u0026#34; in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a Denial of Service(DoS) only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;. XStream has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. This issue affects com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream versions prior to 1.4.21. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the \u0026#34;StackOverflowError\u0026#34; in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a Denial of Service(DoS) only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;. XStream has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. This issue affects com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream versions prior to 1.4.21. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the \u0026#34;StackOverflowError\u0026#34; in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202447072","id":"CVE-2024-47072 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a Denial of Service(DoS) only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;. XStream has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. This issue affects com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream versions prior to 1.4.21. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the \u0026#34;StackOverflowError\u0026#34; in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the \u0026#34;BinaryStreamDriver\u0026#34;.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Generic-Api-Key - generic-api-key (sscs-secret-detection)","name":"Generic-Api-Key","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Remove api-key 375a*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault).","markdown":"Remove api-key 375a*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Detected a Generic API Key, potentially exposing access to various services and sensitive operations."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Generic-Api-Key","id":"Generic-Api-Key - generic-api-key (sscs-secret-detection)","description":"Detected a Generic API Key, potentially exposing access to various services and sensitive operations.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sscs-secret-detection"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-26258 (sca)","name":"Cve202026258","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.15, a Server-Side Forgery Request vulnerability can be activated when unmarshalling. The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.15. The reported vulnerability does not exist if running Java 15 or higher. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework with a whitelist! Anyone relying on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist can immediately switch to a whilelist for the allowed types to avoid the vulnerability. Users of XStream 1.4.14 or below who still want to use XStream default blacklist can use a workaround described in more detailed in the referenced advisories.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.15, a Server-Side Forgery Request vulnerability can be activated when unmarshalling. The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.15. The reported vulnerability does not exist if running Java 15 or higher. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework with a whitelist! Anyone relying on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist can immediately switch to a whilelist for the allowed types to avoid the vulnerability. Users of XStream 1.4.14 or below who still want to use XStream default blacklist can use a workaround described in more detailed in the referenced advisories."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.15, a Server-Side Forgery Request vulnerability can be activated when unmarshalling. The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.15. The reported vulnerability does not exist if running Java 15 or higher. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework with a whitelist! Anyone relying on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist can immediately switch to a whilelist for the allowed types to avoid the vulnerability. Users of XStream 1.4.14 or below who still want to use XStream default blacklist can use a workaround described in more detailed in the referenced advisories."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202026258","id":"CVE-2020-26258 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.15, a Server-Side Forgery Request vulnerability can be activated when unmarshalling. The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.15. The reported vulnerability does not exist if running Java 15 or higher. No user is affected who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s Security Framework with a whitelist! Anyone relying on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist can immediately switch to a whilelist for the allowed types to avoid the vulnerability. Users of XStream 1.4.14 or below who still want to use XStream default blacklist can use a workaround described in more detailed in the referenced advisories.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Absolute Path Traversal - 4635938147065118004 (sast)","name":"Absolute Path Traversal","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Absolute Path Traversal","id":"Absolute Path Traversal - 4635938147065118004 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21351 (sca)","name":"Cve202121351","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121351","id":"CVE-2021-21351 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2016-3674 (sca)","name":"Cve20163674","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Multiple XML external entity (XXE) vulnerabilities in the (1) Dom4JDriver, (2) DomDriver, (3) JDomDriver, (4) JDom2Driver, (5) SjsxpDriver, (6) StandardStaxDriver, and (7) WstxDriver drivers in XStream before 1.4.9 allow remote attackers to read arbitrary files via a crafted XML document.","markdown":"Multiple XML external entity (XXE) vulnerabilities in the (1) Dom4JDriver, (2) DomDriver, (3) JDomDriver, (4) JDom2Driver, (5) SjsxpDriver, (6) StandardStaxDriver, and (7) WstxDriver drivers in XStream before 1.4.9 allow remote attackers to read arbitrary files via a crafted XML document."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Multiple XML external entity (XXE) vulnerabilities in the (1) Dom4JDriver, (2) DomDriver, (3) JDomDriver, (4) JDom2Driver, (5) SjsxpDriver, (6) StandardStaxDriver, and (7) WstxDriver drivers in XStream before 1.4.9 allow remote attackers to read arbitrary files via a crafted XML document."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20163674","id":"CVE-2016-3674 (sca)","description":"Multiple XML external entity (XXE) vulnerabilities in the (1) Dom4JDriver, (2) DomDriver, (3) JDomDriver, (4) JDom2Driver, (5) SjsxpDriver, (6) StandardStaxDriver, and (7) WstxDriver drivers in XStream before 1.4.9 allow remote attackers to read arbitrary files via a crafted XML document.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Hashicorp-Tf-Password - hashicorp-tf-password (sscs-secret-detection)","name":"Hashicorp-Tf-Password","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Remove password \"bm5*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault).","markdown":"Remove password \"bm5*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Identified a HashiCorp Terraform password field, risking unauthorized infrastructure configuration and security breaches."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Hashicorp-Tf-Password","id":"Hashicorp-Tf-Password - hashicorp-tf-password (sscs-secret-detection)","description":"Identified a HashiCorp Terraform password field, risking unauthorized infrastructure configuration and security breaches.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sscs-secret-detection"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21347 (sca)","name":"Cve202121347","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121347","id":"CVE-2021-21347 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-52520 (sca)","name":"Cve202552520","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"For some unlikely configurations of multipart upload, an Integer Overflow vulnerability in Apache Tomcat could lead to a Denial of Service (DoS) via bypassing of size limits.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue.","markdown":"For some unlikely configurations of multipart upload, an Integer Overflow vulnerability in Apache Tomcat could lead to a Denial of Service (DoS) via bypassing of size limits.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"For some unlikely configurations of multipart upload, an Integer Overflow vulnerability in Apache Tomcat could lead to a Denial of Service (DoS) via bypassing of size limits.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202552520","id":"CVE-2025-52520 (sca)","description":"For some unlikely configurations of multipart upload, an Integer Overflow vulnerability in Apache Tomcat could lead to a Denial of Service (DoS) via bypassing of size limits.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21349 (sca)","name":"Cve202121349","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121349","id":"CVE-2021-21349 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to request data from internal resources that are not publicly available only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Missing User Instruction - fd54f200-402c-4333-a5a4-36ef6709af2f [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Missing User Instruction","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Always set a user in the runtime stage of your Dockerfile. Without it, the container defaults to root, even if earlier build stages define a user. Value: The 'Dockerfile' does not contain any 'USER' instruction Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' should contain the 'USER' instruction","markdown":"Always set a user in the runtime stage of your Dockerfile. Without it, the container defaults to root, even if earlier build stages define a user. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e The 'Dockerfile' does not contain any 'USER' instruction \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e The 'Dockerfile' should contain the 'USER' instruction"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Always set a user in the runtime stage of your Dockerfile. Without it, the container defaults to root, even if earlier build stages define a user. Value: The 'Dockerfile' does not contain any 'USER' instruction Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' should contain the 'USER' instruction"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Missing User Instruction","id":"Missing User Instruction - fd54f200-402c-4333-a5a4-36ef6709af2f [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"Always set a user in the runtime stage of your Dockerfile. Without it, the container defaults to root, even if earlier build stages define a user. Value: The 'Dockerfile' does not contain any 'USER' instruction Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' should contain the 'USER' instruction","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21350 (sca)","name":"Cve202121350","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121350","id":"CVE-2021-21350 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21348 (sca)","name":"Cve202121348","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to occupy a thread that consumes maximum CPU time and will never return. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to occupy a thread that consumes maximum CPU time and will never return. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to occupy a thread that consumes maximum CPU time and will never return. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121348","id":"CVE-2021-21348 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to occupy a thread that consumes maximum CPU time and will never return. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21343 (sca)","name":"Cve202121343","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in the deletion of a file on the local host. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in the deletion of a file on the local host. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in the deletion of a file on the local host. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121343","id":"CVE-2021-21343 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability where the processed stream at unmarshalling time contains type information to recreate the formerly written objects. XStream creates therefore new instances based on these type information. An attacker can manipulate the processed input stream and replace or inject objects, that result in the deletion of a file on the local host. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21345 (sca)","name":"Cve202121345","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker who has sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker who has sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker who has sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121345","id":"CVE-2021-21345 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker who has sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21344 (sca)","name":"Cve202121344","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121344","id":"CVE-2021-21344 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-41966 (sca)","name":"Cve202241966","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a Denial-of-Service (DoS) only via manipulation of the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation, causing a stack overflow. Which handles the stack overflow and raises an \u0026#34;InputManipulationException\u0026#34; instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers to these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of \u0026#34;java.util.Map\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;java.util\u0026#34; per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable.","markdown":"XStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a Denial-of-Service (DoS) only via manipulation of the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation, causing a stack overflow. Which handles the stack overflow and raises an \u0026#34;InputManipulationException\u0026#34; instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers to these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of \u0026#34;java.util.Map\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;java.util\u0026#34; per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a Denial-of-Service (DoS) only via manipulation of the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation, causing a stack overflow. Which handles the stack overflow and raises an \u0026#34;InputManipulationException\u0026#34; instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers to these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of \u0026#34;java.util.Map\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;java.util\u0026#34; per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202241966","id":"CVE-2022-41966 (sca)","description":"XStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a Denial-of-Service (DoS) only via manipulation of the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation, causing a stack overflow. Which handles the stack overflow and raises an \u0026#34;InputManipulationException\u0026#34; instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers to these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of \u0026#34;java.util.Map\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;java.util\u0026#34; per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-48988 (sca)","name":"Cve202548988","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in Apache Tomcat. \nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.105, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.41 and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.7. Users are advised to upgrade to a version that includes the fix to mitigate this vulnerability.","markdown":"Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in Apache Tomcat. \nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.105, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.41 and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.7. Users are advised to upgrade to a version that includes the fix to mitigate this vulnerability."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in Apache Tomcat. \nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.105, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.41 and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.7. Users are advised to upgrade to a version that includes the fix to mitigate this vulnerability."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202548988","id":"CVE-2025-48988 (sca)","description":"Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in Apache Tomcat. \nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.105, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.41 and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.7. Users are advised to upgrade to a version that includes the fix to mitigate this vulnerability.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-31650 (sca)","name":"Cve202531650","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Improper Input Validation vulnerability was found in Apache Tomcat. Incorrect error handling for some invalid HTTP priority headers resulted in incomplete clean-up of the failed request which created a memory leak. A large number of such requests could trigger an \u0026#34;OutOfMemoryException\u0026#34; resulting in a Denial-Of-Service (DOS).\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 9.0.76 through 9.0.102, from 10.1.10 through 10.1.39, from 11.0.0-M2 through 11.0.5.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 9.0.104, 10.1.40 or 11.0.6 which fixes the issue.","markdown":"Improper Input Validation vulnerability was found in Apache Tomcat. Incorrect error handling for some invalid HTTP priority headers resulted in incomplete clean-up of the failed request which created a memory leak. A large number of such requests could trigger an \u0026#34;OutOfMemoryException\u0026#34; resulting in a Denial-Of-Service (DOS).\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 9.0.76 through 9.0.102, from 10.1.10 through 10.1.39, from 11.0.0-M2 through 11.0.5.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 9.0.104, 10.1.40 or 11.0.6 which fixes the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Improper Input Validation vulnerability was found in Apache Tomcat. Incorrect error handling for some invalid HTTP priority headers resulted in incomplete clean-up of the failed request which created a memory leak. A large number of such requests could trigger an \u0026#34;OutOfMemoryException\u0026#34; resulting in a Denial-Of-Service (DOS).\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 9.0.76 through 9.0.102, from 10.1.10 through 10.1.39, from 11.0.0-M2 through 11.0.5.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 9.0.104, 10.1.40 or 11.0.6 which fixes the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202531650","id":"CVE-2025-31650 (sca)","description":"Improper Input Validation vulnerability was found in Apache Tomcat. Incorrect error handling for some invalid HTTP priority headers resulted in incomplete clean-up of the failed request which created a memory leak. A large number of such requests could trigger an \u0026#34;OutOfMemoryException\u0026#34; resulting in a Denial-Of-Service (DOS).\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 9.0.76 through 9.0.102, from 10.1.10 through 10.1.39, from 11.0.0-M2 through 11.0.5.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 9.0.104, 10.1.40 or 11.0.6 which fixes the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39147 (sca)","name":"Cve202139147","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139147","id":"CVE-2021-39147 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39148 (sca)","name":"Cve202139148","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139148","id":"CVE-2021-39148 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39145 (sca)","name":"Cve202139145","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139145","id":"CVE-2021-39145 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-53506 (sca)","name":"Cve202553506","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in Apache Tomcat if an HTTP/2 client did not acknowledge the initial settings frame that reduces the maximum permitted concurrent streams.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue.","markdown":"Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in Apache Tomcat if an HTTP/2 client did not acknowledge the initial settings frame that reduces the maximum permitted concurrent streams.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in Apache Tomcat if an HTTP/2 client did not acknowledge the initial settings frame that reduces the maximum permitted concurrent streams.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202553506","id":"CVE-2025-53506 (sca)","description":"Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in Apache Tomcat if an HTTP/2 client did not acknowledge the initial settings frame that reduces the maximum permitted concurrent streams.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat versions from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.8, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.42, from 9.0.0.M1 through 9.0.106.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.9, 10.1.43 or 9.0.107, which fix the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-48989 (sca)","name":"Cve202548989","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Improper Resource Shutdown or Release vulnerability in Apache Tomcat made Tomcat vulnerable to the made you reset attack. This issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 8.5.0  through 9.0.107, 10.0.0-M1 through 10.1.43, and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.9. Older, EOL versions may also be affected.","markdown":"Improper Resource Shutdown or Release vulnerability in Apache Tomcat made Tomcat vulnerable to the made you reset attack. This issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 8.5.0  through 9.0.107, 10.0.0-M1 through 10.1.43, and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.9. Older, EOL versions may also be affected."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Improper Resource Shutdown or Release vulnerability in Apache Tomcat made Tomcat vulnerable to the made you reset attack. This issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 8.5.0  through 9.0.107, 10.0.0-M1 through 10.1.43, and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.9. Older, EOL versions may also be affected."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202548989","id":"CVE-2025-48989 (sca)","description":"Improper Resource Shutdown or Release vulnerability in Apache Tomcat made Tomcat vulnerable to the made you reset attack. This issue affects Apache Tomcat versions 8.5.0  through 9.0.107, 10.0.0-M1 through 10.1.43, and 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.9. Older, EOL versions may also be affected.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-41232 (sca)","name":"Cve202541232","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Spring Security Aspects may not correctly detect method security annotations on private methods, potentially leading to authorization bypasses. An application may be affected if both of the following conditions are met: a) the configuration includes `@EnableMethodSecurity(mode = ASPECTJ)` and the \u0026#34;spring-security-aspects\u0026#34; module, b) one or more private methods are annotated with Spring Security method-level annotations. Under these conditions, the affected methods may be invoked without the expected authorization checks. This vulnerability affects org.springframework.security:spring-security-core package versions 6.4.x prior to 6.4.6, 6.5.x prior to 6.5.0.","markdown":"Spring Security Aspects may not correctly detect method security annotations on private methods, potentially leading to authorization bypasses. An application may be affected if both of the following conditions are met: a) the configuration includes `@EnableMethodSecurity(mode = ASPECTJ)` and the \u0026#34;spring-security-aspects\u0026#34; module, b) one or more private methods are annotated with Spring Security method-level annotations. Under these conditions, the affected methods may be invoked without the expected authorization checks. This vulnerability affects org.springframework.security:spring-security-core package versions 6.4.x prior to 6.4.6, 6.5.x prior to 6.5.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Spring Security Aspects may not correctly detect method security annotations on private methods, potentially leading to authorization bypasses. An application may be affected if both of the following conditions are met: a) the configuration includes `@EnableMethodSecurity(mode = ASPECTJ)` and the \u0026#34;spring-security-aspects\u0026#34; module, b) one or more private methods are annotated with Spring Security method-level annotations. Under these conditions, the affected methods may be invoked without the expected authorization checks. This vulnerability affects org.springframework.security:spring-security-core package versions 6.4.x prior to 6.4.6, 6.5.x prior to 6.5.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202541232","id":"CVE-2025-41232 (sca)","description":"Spring Security Aspects may not correctly detect method security annotations on private methods, potentially leading to authorization bypasses. An application may be affected if both of the following conditions are met: a) the configuration includes `@EnableMethodSecurity(mode = ASPECTJ)` and the \u0026#34;spring-security-aspects\u0026#34; module, b) one or more private methods are annotated with Spring Security method-level annotations. Under these conditions, the affected methods may be invoked without the expected authorization checks. This vulnerability affects org.springframework.security:spring-security-core package versions 6.4.x prior to 6.4.6, 6.5.x prior to 6.5.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-24813 (sca)","name":"Cve202524813","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Path Equivalence: \u0026#39;file.Name\u0026#39; (Internal Dot) leading to Remote Code Execution and/or Information disclosure and/or malicious content added to uploaded files via write-enabled Default Servlet in Apache Tomcat.This issue affects Apache Tomcat: through version 9.0.98, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.34, 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.2.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to view security-sensitive files and/or inject content into those files: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), a target URL for security-sensitive uploads that was a subdirectory of a target URL for public uploads, attacker knowledge of the names of security-sensitive files being uploaded, the security sensitive files also being uploaded via partial PUT.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to perform remote code execution: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), application was using Tomcat\u0026#39;s file-based session persistence with the default storage location, application included a library that may be leveraged in a deserialization attack.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.3, 10.1.35 or 9.0.99, which fixes the issue.","markdown":"Path Equivalence: \u0026#39;file.Name\u0026#39; (Internal Dot) leading to Remote Code Execution and/or Information disclosure and/or malicious content added to uploaded files via write-enabled Default Servlet in Apache Tomcat.This issue affects Apache Tomcat: through version 9.0.98, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.34, 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.2.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to view security-sensitive files and/or inject content into those files: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), a target URL for security-sensitive uploads that was a subdirectory of a target URL for public uploads, attacker knowledge of the names of security-sensitive files being uploaded, the security sensitive files also being uploaded via partial PUT.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to perform remote code execution: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), application was using Tomcat\u0026#39;s file-based session persistence with the default storage location, application included a library that may be leveraged in a deserialization attack.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.3, 10.1.35 or 9.0.99, which fixes the issue."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Path Equivalence: \u0026#39;file.Name\u0026#39; (Internal Dot) leading to Remote Code Execution and/or Information disclosure and/or malicious content added to uploaded files via write-enabled Default Servlet in Apache Tomcat.This issue affects Apache Tomcat: through version 9.0.98, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.34, 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.2.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to view security-sensitive files and/or inject content into those files: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), a target URL for security-sensitive uploads that was a subdirectory of a target URL for public uploads, attacker knowledge of the names of security-sensitive files being uploaded, the security sensitive files also being uploaded via partial PUT.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to perform remote code execution: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), application was using Tomcat\u0026#39;s file-based session persistence with the default storage location, application included a library that may be leveraged in a deserialization attack.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.3, 10.1.35 or 9.0.99, which fixes the issue."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202524813","id":"CVE-2025-24813 (sca)","description":"Path Equivalence: \u0026#39;file.Name\u0026#39; (Internal Dot) leading to Remote Code Execution and/or Information disclosure and/or malicious content added to uploaded files via write-enabled Default Servlet in Apache Tomcat.This issue affects Apache Tomcat: through version 9.0.98, 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.34, 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.2.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to view security-sensitive files and/or inject content into those files: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), a target URL for security-sensitive uploads that was a subdirectory of a target URL for public uploads, attacker knowledge of the names of security-sensitive files being uploaded, the security sensitive files also being uploaded via partial PUT.\n\nIf all of the following were true, a malicious user was able to perform remote code execution: writes enabled for the default servlet (disabled by default), support for partial PUT (enabled by default), application was using Tomcat\u0026#39;s file-based session persistence with the default storage location, application included a library that may be leveraged in a deserialization attack.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.3, 10.1.35 or 9.0.99, which fixes the issue.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-21346 (sca)","name":"Cve202121346","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","markdown":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202121346","id":"CVE-2021-21346 (sca)","description":"XStream is a Java library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In XStream before version 1.4.16, there is a vulnerability which may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. If you rely on XStream\u0026#39;s default blacklist of the Security Framework, you will have to use at least version 1.4.16.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2023-51775 (sca)","name":"Cve202351775","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The jose4j component prior to 0.9.4 for Java allows attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) via a large p2c (aka PBES2 Count) value.","markdown":"The jose4j component prior to 0.9.4 for Java allows attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) via a large p2c (aka PBES2 Count) value."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The jose4j component prior to 0.9.4 for Java allows attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) via a large p2c (aka PBES2 Count) value."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202351775","id":"CVE-2023-51775 (sca)","description":"The jose4j component prior to 0.9.4 for Java allows attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) via a large p2c (aka PBES2 Count) value.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-29505 (sca)","name":"Cve202129505","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a software for serializing Java objects to XML and back again. A vulnerability in XStream versions prior to 1.4.17 may allow a remote attacker with sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types is affected. The vulnerability is patched in version 1.4.17.","markdown":"XStream is a software for serializing Java objects to XML and back again. A vulnerability in XStream versions prior to 1.4.17 may allow a remote attacker with sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types is affected. The vulnerability is patched in version 1.4.17."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a software for serializing Java objects to XML and back again. A vulnerability in XStream versions prior to 1.4.17 may allow a remote attacker with sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types is affected. The vulnerability is patched in version 1.4.17."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202129505","id":"CVE-2021-29505 (sca)","description":"XStream is a software for serializing Java objects to XML and back again. A vulnerability in XStream versions prior to 1.4.17 may allow a remote attacker with sufficient rights to execute commands of the host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types is affected. The vulnerability is patched in version 1.4.17.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39149 (sca)","name":"Cve202139149","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","markdown":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"fullDescription":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202139149","id":"CVE-2021-39149 (sca)","description":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. In affected versions this vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to load and execute arbitrary code from a remote host only by manipulating the processed input stream. No user is affected, who followed the recommendation to setup XStream\u0026#39;s security framework with a whitelist limited to the minimal required types. XStream 1.4.18 uses no longer a blacklist by default, since it cannot be secured for general purpose.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-39141 (sca)","name":"Cve202139141","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XM