re Through an Error Message","id":"Information Exposure Through an Error Message - 2701599985492857111 (sast)","description":"Method commence, at line 54 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/AjaxAuthenticationEntryPoint.java, handles an Exception or runtime Error authException. During the exception handling code, the application exposes the exception details to sendError, in method commence of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/container/AjaxAuthenticationEntryPoint.java, line 54.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-30258 (containers)","name":"Cve202530258","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"In GnuPG before 2.5.5, if a user chooses to import a certificate with certain crafted subkey data that lacks a valid backsig or that has incorrect usage flags, the user loses the ability to verify signatures made from certain other signing keys, aka a \u0026#34;verification DoS.\u0026#34;","markdown":"In GnuPG before 2.5.5, if a user chooses to import a certificate with certain crafted subkey data that lacks a valid backsig or that has incorrect usage flags, the user loses the ability to verify signatures made from certain other signing keys, aka a \u0026#34;verification DoS.\u0026#34;"},"fullDescription":{"text":"In GnuPG before 2.5.5, if a user chooses to import a certificate with certain crafted subkey data that lacks a valid backsig or that has incorrect usage flags, the user loses the ability to verify signatures made from certain other signing keys, aka a \u0026#34;verification DoS.\u0026#34;"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve202530258","id":"CVE-2025-30258 (containers)","description":"In GnuPG before 2.5.5, if a user chooses to import a certificate with certain crafted subkey data that lacks a valid backsig or that has incorrect usage flags, the user loses the ability to verify signatures made from certain other signing keys, aka a \u0026#34;verification DoS.\u0026#34;","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-1182 (containers)","name":"Cve20251182","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A vulnerability, which was classified as critical, was found in GNU Binutils. Affected is the function \u0026#34;bfd_elf_reloc_symbol_deleted_p\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;bfd/elflink.c\u0026#34; of the component ld. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. It is possible to launch the attack remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitability is told to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.","markdown":"A vulnerability, which was classified as critical, was found in GNU Binutils. Affected is the function \u0026#34;bfd_elf_reloc_symbol_deleted_p\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;bfd/elflink.c\u0026#34; of the component ld. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. It is possible to launch the attack remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitability is told to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A vulnerability, which was classified as critical, was found in GNU Binutils. Affected is the function \u0026#34;bfd_elf_reloc_symbol_deleted_p\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;bfd/elflink.c\u0026#34; of the component ld. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. It is possible to launch the attack remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitability is told to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve20251182","id":"CVE-2025-1182 (containers)","description":"A vulnerability, which was classified as critical, was found in GNU Binutils. Affected is the function \u0026#34;bfd_elf_reloc_symbol_deleted_p\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;bfd/elflink.c\u0026#34; of the component ld. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. It is possible to launch the attack remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitability is told to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-1176 (containers)","name":"Cve20251176","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A vulnerability has been discovered in GNU Binutils, specifically in the function \u0026#34;_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec\u0026#34; within the \u0026#34;elflink.c\u0026#34; file of the \u0026#34;ld\u0026#34; component. This issue can lead to a heap-based buffer overflow, which may be exploited remotely. The complexity of exploiting this vulnerability is relatively high, and its exploitation is known to be difficult. However, the exploit has been publicly disclosed and could potentially be used by attackers. To mitigate this issue, it is strongly recommended to apply the patch.","markdown":"A vulnerability has been discovered in GNU Binutils, specifically in the function \u0026#34;_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec\u0026#34; within the \u0026#34;elflink.c\u0026#34; file of the \u0026#34;ld\u0026#34; component. This issue can lead to a heap-based buffer overflow, which may be exploited remotely. The complexity of exploiting this vulnerability is relatively high, and its exploitation is known to be difficult. However, the exploit has been publicly disclosed and could potentially be used by attackers. To mitigate this issue, it is strongly recommended to apply the patch."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A vulnerability has been discovered in GNU Binutils, specifically in the function \u0026#34;_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec\u0026#34; within the \u0026#34;elflink.c\u0026#34; file of the \u0026#34;ld\u0026#34; component. This issue can lead to a heap-based buffer overflow, which may be exploited remotely. The complexity of exploiting this vulnerability is relatively high, and its exploitation is known to be difficult. However, the exploit has been publicly disclosed and could potentially be used by attackers. To mitigate this issue, it is strongly recommended to apply the patch."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve20251176","id":"CVE-2025-1176 (containers)","description":"A vulnerability has been discovered in GNU Binutils, specifically in the function \u0026#34;_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec\u0026#34; within the \u0026#34;elflink.c\u0026#34; file of the \u0026#34;ld\u0026#34; component. This issue can lead to a heap-based buffer overflow, which may be exploited remotely. The complexity of exploiting this vulnerability is relatively high, and its exploitation is known to be difficult. However, the exploit has been publicly disclosed and could potentially be used by attackers. To mitigate this issue, it is strongly recommended to apply the patch.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-1181 (containers)","name":"Cve20251181","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A vulnerability classified as critical was found in GNU Binutils. This vulnerability affects the function `_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec` of the file `bfd/elflink.c` of the component `ld`. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be initiated remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.","markdown":"A vulnerability classified as critical was found in GNU Binutils. This vulnerability affects the function `_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec` of the file `bfd/elflink.c` of the component `ld`. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be initiated remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A vulnerability classified as critical was found in GNU Binutils. This vulnerability affects the function `_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec` of the file `bfd/elflink.c` of the component `ld`. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be initiated remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve20251181","id":"CVE-2025-1181 (containers)","description":"A vulnerability classified as critical was found in GNU Binutils. This vulnerability affects the function `_bfd_elf_gc_mark_rsec` of the file `bfd/elflink.c` of the component `ld`. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be initiated remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-1153 (containers)","name":"Cve20251153","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in GNU Binutils versions 2.31 through 2.43.1. Affected by this vulnerability is the function \u0026#34;bfd_set_format\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;format.c\u0026#34;. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be launched remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. Upgrading to version 2.45 is able to address this issue. The identifier of the patch is 8d97c1a53f3dc9fd8e1ccdb039b8a33d50133150. It is recommended to upgrade the affected component.","markdown":"A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in GNU Binutils versions 2.31 through 2.43.1. Affected by this vulnerability is the function \u0026#34;bfd_set_format\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;format.c\u0026#34;. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be launched remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. Upgrading to version 2.45 is able to address this issue. The identifier of the patch is 8d97c1a53f3dc9fd8e1ccdb039b8a33d50133150. It is recommended to upgrade the affected component."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in GNU Binutils versions 2.31 through 2.43.1. Affected by this vulnerability is the function \u0026#34;bfd_set_format\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;format.c\u0026#34;. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be launched remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. Upgrading to version 2.45 is able to address this issue. The identifier of the patch is 8d97c1a53f3dc9fd8e1ccdb039b8a33d50133150. It is recommended to upgrade the affected component."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve20251153","id":"CVE-2025-1153 (containers)","description":"A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in GNU Binutils versions 2.31 through 2.43.1. Affected by this vulnerability is the function \u0026#34;bfd_set_format\u0026#34; of the file \u0026#34;format.c\u0026#34;. The manipulation leads to memory corruption. The attack can be launched remotely. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. Upgrading to version 2.45 is able to address this issue. The identifier of the patch is 8d97c1a53f3dc9fd8e1ccdb039b8a33d50133150. It is recommended to upgrade the affected component.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"Secret Leak in Error Messages - 7748541724187880017 (sast)","name":"Secret Leak in Error Messages","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method Lambda at line 4465 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webgoat/static/js/libs/ace.js includes the secret in Error in the error message. This may result in a 