506624030647 (sast)","description":"Method follow at line 77 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/jwt/JWTRefreshEndpoint.java defines password, which is designated to contain user passwords. However, while plaintext passwords are later assigned to password, this variable is never cleared from memory.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Missing CSP Header - 729519850006803664 (sast)","name":"Missing CSP Header","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n","markdown":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Missing CSP Header","id":"Missing CSP Header - 729519850006803664 (sast)","description":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Unsynchronized Access To Shared Data - 8148341358233039975 (sast)","name":"Unsynchronized Access To Shared Data","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The concurrent process CxStaticBlock1 found in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61 influences the shared resource fmt in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61. When performed concurrently, an unexpected race condition may occur.\n\n","markdown":"The concurrent process CxStaticBlock1 found in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61 influences the shared resource fmt in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61. When performed concurrently, an unexpected race condition may occur.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The concurrent process CxStaticBlock1 found in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61 influences the shared resource fmt in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61. When performed concurrently, an unexpected race condition may occur.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Unsynchronized Access To Shared Data","id":"Unsynchronized Access To Shared Data - 8148341358233039975 (sast)","description":"The concurrent process CxStaticBlock1 found in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61 influences the shared resource fmt in the file /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/ForgedReviews.java at line 61. When performed concurrently, an unexpected race condition may occur.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Creation of Temp File in Dir with Incorrect Permissions - 13074046093827725135 (sast)","name":"Creation of Temp File in Dir with Incorrect Permissions","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Creation of Temp File in Dir with Incorrect Permissions","id":"Creation of Temp File in Dir with Incorrect Permissions - 13074046093827725135 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-22233 (sca)","name":"Cve202522233","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"CVE-2024-38820 ensured locale-independent, lowercase conversion for both the configured \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; patterns and for request parameter names. However, there are still cases where it is possible to bypass the \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; checks. Generally, it is recommended to use a dedicated model object with properties only for data binding or to use constructor binding, since constructor arguments explicitly declare what to bind, together with turning off setter binding through the \u0026#34;declarativeBinding\u0026#34; flag. See the Model Design section in the reference documentation. For setter binding, prefer using \u0026#34;allowedFields\u0026#34; (an explicit list) over \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34;. This issue affects org.springframework:spring-context versions through 5.3.39-atlassian-4, 6.0.0-M1 through 6.0.23, 6.1.0-M1 through 6.1.19, 6.2.0-M1 through 6.2.6, and 7.0.0-M1 through 7.0.0-M4. Credit: This issue was responsibly reported by the TERASOLUNA Framework Development Team from NTT DATA Group Corporation.","markdown":"CVE-2024-38820 ensured locale-independent, lowercase conversion for both the configured \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; patterns and for request parameter names. However, there are still cases where it is possible to bypass the \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; checks. Generally, it is recommended to use a dedicated model object with properties only for data binding or to use constructor binding, since constructor arguments explicitly declare what to bind, together with turning off setter binding through the \u0026#34;declarativeBinding\u0026#34; flag. See the Model Design section in the reference documentation. For setter binding, prefer using \u0026#34;allowedFields\u0026#34; (an explicit list) over \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34;. This issue affects org.springframework:spring-context versions through 5.3.39-atlassian-4, 6.0.0-M1 through 6.0.23, 6.1.0-M1 through 6.1.19, 6.2.0-M1 through 6.2.6, and 7.0.0-M1 through 7.0.0-M4. Credit: This issue was responsibly reported by the TERASOLUNA Framework Development Team from NTT DATA Group Corporation."},"fullDescription":{"text":"CVE-2024-38820 ensured locale-independent, lowercase conversion for both the configured \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; patterns and for request parameter names. However, there are still cases where it is possible to bypass the \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; checks. Generally, it is recommended to use a dedicated model object with properties only for data binding or to use constructor binding, since constructor arguments explicitly declare what to bind, together with turning off setter binding through the \u0026#34;declarativeBinding\u0026#34; flag. See the Model Design section in the reference documentation. For setter binding, prefer using \u0026#34;allowedFields\u0026#34; (an explicit list) over \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34;. This issue affects org.springframework:spring-context versions through 5.3.39-atlassian-4, 6.0.0-M1 through 6.0.23, 6.1.0-M1 through 6.1.19, 6.2.0-M1 through 6.2.6, and 7.0.0-M1 through 7.0.0-M4. Credit: This issue was responsibly reported by the TERASOLUNA Framework Development Team from NTT DATA Group Corporation."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve202522233","id":"CVE-2025-22233 (sca)","description":"CVE-2024-38820 ensured locale-independent, lowercase conversion for both the configured \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; patterns and for request parameter names. However, there are still cases where it is possible to bypass the \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34; checks. Generally, it is recommended to use a dedicated model object with properties only for data binding or to use constructor binding, since constructor arguments explicitly declare what to bind, together with turning off setter binding through the \u0026#34;declarativeBinding\u0026#34; flag. See the Model Design section in the reference documentation. For setter binding, prefer using \u0026#34;allowedFields\u0026#34; (an explicit list) over \u0026#34;disallowedFields\u0026#34;. This issue affects org.springframework:spring-context versions through 5.3.39-atlassian-4, 6.0.0-M1 through 6.0.23, 6.1.0-M1 through 6.1.19, 6.2.0-M1 through 6.2.6, and 7.0.0-M1 through 7.0.0-M4. Credit: This issue was responsibly reported by the TERASOLUNA Framework Development Team from NTT DATA Group Corporation.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Improper Transaction Handling - 2423463851877241103 (sast)","name":"Improper Transaction Handling","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s injectableQuery method in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/sqlinjection/introduction/SqlInjectionLesson4.java creates and opens a connection to the database, and enlists it in a transaction. Though the application wraps the connection in a `try { }` block to handle exceptions, the database transaction is not always rolled back on errors.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s injectableQuery method in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/sqlinjection/introduction/SqlInjectionLesson4.java creates and opens a connection to the database, and enlists it in a transaction. Though the application wraps the connection in a `try { }` block to handle exceptions, the database transaction is not always rolled back on errors.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s injectableQuery method in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/sqlinjection/introduction/SqlInjectionLesson4.java creates and opens a connection to the database, and enlists it in a transaction. Though the application wraps the connection in a `try { }` block to handle exceptions, the database transaction is not always rolled back on errors.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Improper Transaction Handling","id":"Improper Transaction Handling - 2423463851877241103 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s injectableQuery method in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/sqlinjection/introduction/SqlInjectionLesson4.java creates and opens a connection to the database, and enlists it in a transaction. Though the application wraps the connection in a `try { }` block to handle exceptions, the database transaction is not always rolled back on errors.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Chown Flag Exists - aa93e17f-b6db-4162-9334-c70334e7ac28 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Chown Flag Exists","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"It is considered a best practice for every executable in a container to be owned by the root user even if it is executed by a non-root user, only execution permissions are required on the file, not ownership Value: The 'Dockerfile' contains the 'chown' flag Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' shouldn´t contain the 'chown' flag","markdown":"It is considered a best practice for every executable in a container to be owned by the root user even if it is executed by a non-root user, only execution permissions are required on the file, not ownership \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e The 'Dockerfile' contains the 'chown' flag \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e The 'Dockerfile' shouldn´t contain the 'chown' flag"},"fullDescription":{"text":"It is considered a best practice for every executable in a container to be owned by the root user even if it is executed by a non-root user, only execution permissions are required on the file, not ownership Value: The 'Dockerfile' contains the 'chown' flag Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' shouldn´t contain the 'chown' flag"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Chown Flag Exists","id":"Chown Flag Exists - aa93e17f-b6db-4162-9334-c70334e7ac28 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"It is considered a best practice for every executable in a container to be owned by the root user even if it is executed by a non-root user, only execution permissions are required on the file, not ownership Value: The 'Dockerfile' contains the 'chown' flag Excepted value: The 'Dockerfile' shouldn´t contain the 'chown' flag","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"Client Use Of Iframe Without Sandbox - 12151859793050070545 (sast)","name":"Client Use Of Iframe Without Sandbox","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application employs an HTML iframe at whose contents are not properly sandboxed","markdown":"The application employs an HTML iframe at whose contents are not properly sandboxed"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application employs an HTML iframe at whose contents are not properly sandboxed"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Client Use Of Iframe Without Sandbox","id":"Client Use Of Iframe Without Sandbox - 12151859793050070545 (sast)","description":"The application employs an HTML iframe at whose contents are not properly sandboxed","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Spring Missing Content Security Policy - 1421882572503292919 (sast)","name":"Spring Missing Content Security Policy","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n","markdown":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Spring Missing Content Security Policy","id":"Spring Missing Content Security Policy - 1421882572503292919 (sast)","description":"A Content Security Policy is not explicitly defined within the web-application.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Secret Leak in Logs - 17585295581080959833 (sast)","name":"Secret Leak in Logs","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js leaks the secret log to the log.\n\n","markdown":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js leaks the secret log to the log.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js leaks the secret log to the log.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Secret Leak in Logs","id":"Secret Leak in Logs - 17585295581080959833 (sast)","description":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js leaks the secret log to the log.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Healthcheck Instruction Missing - b03a748a-542d-44f4-bb86-9199ab4fd2d5 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Healthcheck Instruction Missing","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Ensure that HEALTHCHECK is being used. The HEALTHCHECK instruction tells Docker how to test a container to check that it is still working Value: Dockerfile doesn't contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK' Excepted value: Dockerfile should contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK'","markdown":"Ensure that HEALTHCHECK is being used. The HEALTHCHECK instruction tells Docker how to test a container to check that it is still working \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e Dockerfile doesn't contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK' \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e Dockerfile should contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK'"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Ensure that HEALTHCHECK is being used. The HEALTHCHECK instruction tells Docker how to test a container to check that it is still working Value: Dockerfile doesn't contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK' Excepted value: Dockerfile should contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK'"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Healthcheck Instruction Missing","id":"Healthcheck Instruction Missing - b03a748a-542d-44f4-bb86-9199ab4fd2d5 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"Ensure that HEALTHCHECK is being used. The HEALTHCHECK instruction tells Docker how to test a container to check that it is still working Value: Dockerfile doesn't contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK' Excepted value: Dockerfile should contain instruction 'HEALTHCHECK'","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"CVE-2024-12801 (sca)","name":"Cve202412801","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) in \u0026#34;SaxEventRecorder\u0026#34; by QOS.CH logback on the Java platform, allows an attacker to forge requests by compromising logback configuration files in XML. The attack involves the modification of \u0026#34;DOCTYPE\u0026#34; declaration in XML configuration files. This issue affects \n ch.qos.logback:logback-core package versions through 1.3.14, and 1.4.0 through 1.5.12.","markdown":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) in \u0026#34;SaxEventRecorder\u0026#34; by QOS.CH logback on the Java platform, allows an attacker to forge requests by compromising logback configuration files in XML. The attack involves the modification of \u0026#34;DOCTYPE\u0026#34; declaration in XML configuration files. This issue affects \n ch.qos.logback:logback-core package versions through 1.3.14, and 1.4.0 through 1.5.12."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) in \u0026#34;SaxEventRecorder\u0026#34; by QOS.CH logback on the Java platform, allows an attacker to forge requests by compromising logback configuration files in XML. The attack involves the modification of \u0026#34;DOCTYPE\u0026#34; declaration in XML configuration files. This issue affects \n ch.qos.logback:logback-core package versions through 1.3.14, and 1.4.0 through 1.5.12."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve202412801","id":"CVE-2024-12801 (sca)","description":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) in \u0026#34;SaxEventRecorder\u0026#34; by QOS.CH logback on the Java platform, allows an attacker to forge requests by compromising logback configuration files in XML. The attack involves the modification of \u0026#34;DOCTYPE\u0026#34; declaration in XML configuration files. This issue affects \n ch.qos.logback:logback-core package versions through 1.3.14, and 1.4.0 through 1.5.12.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Potential Clickjacking on Legacy Browsers - 4267131875844504913 (sast)","name":"Potential Clickjacking on Legacy Browsers","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application does not protect the web page /WebGoat-main/docs/index.html from clickjacking attacks in legacy browsers, by using framebusting scripts.","markdown":"The application does not protect the web page /WebGoat-main/docs/index.html from clickjacking attacks in legacy browsers, by using framebusting scripts."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application does not protect the web page /WebGoat-main/docs/index.html from clickjacking attacks in legacy browsers, by using framebusting scripts."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Potential Clickjacking on Legacy Browsers","id":"Potential Clickjacking on Legacy Browsers - 4267131875844504913 (sast)","description":"The application does not protect the web page /WebGoat-main/docs/index.html from clickjacking attacks in legacy browsers, by using framebusting scripts.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Privacy Violation in Logs - 3182302867849403757 (sast)","name":"Privacy Violation in Logs","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js writes the PII from log to the log. This may result in a Privacy Violation.\n\n","markdown":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js writes the PII from log to the log. This may result in a Privacy Violation.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js writes the PII from log to the log. This may result in a Privacy Violation.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Privacy Violation in Logs","id":"Privacy Violation in Logs - 3182302867849403757 (sast)","description":"Method call at line 50 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/resources/webwolf/static/js/jwt.js writes the PII from log to the log. This may result in a Privacy Violation.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Trust Boundary Violation in Session Variables - 9001657640014870111 (sast)","name":"Trust Boundary Violation in Session Variables","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method getBasicAuth at line 49 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java gets user input from element request. This element’s value flows through the code without being properly sanitized or validated and is eventually stored in the server-side Session object, in getBasicAuth at line 57 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java. This constitutes a Trust Boundary Violation.\n\n","markdown":"Method getBasicAuth at line 49 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java gets user input from element request. This element’s value flows through the code without being properly sanitized or validated and is eventually stored in the server-side Session object, in getBasicAuth at line 57 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java. This constitutes a Trust Boundary Violation.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method getBasicAuth at line 49 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java gets user input from element request. This element’s value flows through the code without being properly sanitized or validated and is eventually stored in the server-side Session object, in getBasicAuth at line 57 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java. This constitutes a Trust Boundary Violation.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Trust Boundary Violation in Session Variables","id":"Trust Boundary Violation in Session Variables - 9001657640014870111 (sast)","description":"Method getBasicAuth at line 49 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java gets user input from element request. This element’s value flows through the code without being properly sanitized or validated and is eventually stored in the server-side Session object, in getBasicAuth at line 57 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/cryptography/EncodingAssignment.java. This constitutes a Trust Boundary Violation.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Use of Non Cryptographic Random - 11275104079425393675 (sast)","name":"Use of Non Cryptographic Random","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method invoke at line 75 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/CSRFGetFlag.java uses a weak method nextInt to produce random values. These values are then used as cryptographic variables by invoke at line 75 in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/CSRFGetFlag.java.\n\n","markdown":"Method invoke at line 75 of /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/CSRFGetFlag.java uses a weak method nextInt to produce random values. These values are then used as cryptographic variables by invoke at line 75 in /WebGoat-main/src/main/java/org/owasp/webgoat/lessons/csrf/CSRFGetFlag.java.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"tex